 The Senate on Tuesday received a request from President Muhammadu Buhari for an approval to pay Kogi State Government N10.069 billion being a refund of money spent by the state on behalf of Federal government. The request was contained in a letter dated 10th October 2019 and read by the President of the Senate, Ahmad Ibrahim Lawan, during plenary. The requested amount is for the settlement of inherited local debts and contractual obligations of the Federal Government to the State for projects executed on behalf of the Federal Government. Continue reading Buhari seeks N’Assembly’s approval for N10.06bn refund to Kogi govt at Vanguard Nigeria. Source: Vanguard